text: Assis Brasil is a Brazilian municipality in the state of Acre. In 2007, 5,351 people lived there. Its total area is 2,875,915 km². Vicente Bessa founded the municipality on March 1, 1976. It was separated from another municipality called Brasiléia. Category:Municipalities in Acre (state) Category:1976 establishments in Brazil
title: Assis Brasil
